text:
Dunno whether or not this is an intended thing, but I recently experienced some 
problem when replacing version 0.9.1 with the 1.0 release.
Apparently a very first call to the BasicConfigurator enableAll() method ends 
up with the DEBUG and INFO priorites being disabled !!

Code sample :

org.apache.log4j.BasicConfigurator.enableAll();
org.apache.log4j.Category c = org.apache.log4j.Category.getInstance("Toto");
c.debug("Hello world !");
c.info("Hello world !");
c.warn("Hello world !");
c.error("Hello world !");
c.fatal("Hello world !");

results in displaying :

160  WARN  [main]                                  Toto     - Hello world !
571  ERROR [main]                                  Toto     - Hello world !
601  FATAL [main]                                  Toto     - Hello world !

I know this API is deprecated, but it looks strange to me that such an 
unexpected bug appears !!

Laurent
